# Normalise line endings on checkin for everything git detects as text.
* text=auto

# Force a textual diff for source and docs, whatever bytes they contain.
#
# Git otherwise classifies a file as binary the moment it finds a NUL byte
# and renders it as "Binary file not shown" — silently, during review. Not
# hypothetical: a NUL used as a string separator in src/db/apply-tags.ts
# hid that file's entire diff from PR #25, and it was the one file the PR
# most needed reviewed. The bytes are gone; this makes the failure mode
# impossible to repeat.
*.ts   diff
*.tsx  diff
*.js   diff
*.mjs  diff
*.json diff
*.md   diff
*.css  diff
*.sql  diff
*.yml  diff
*.yaml diff
